@startuml ansible
title dropicture - Ansible provisioning (single-node Docker Swarm)
footer Author: Amir Redjem   |   2026-06-05   |   v1.2

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam ArrowColor #2F6FED
skinparam ArrowFontColor #41505F
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FDF4F4
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #E6BCBC
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #EEF4FF
skinparam ActorBorderColor #B8CDF3
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #B7E0C9
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #B8C4D0
skinparam SequenceDividerBackgroundColor #EEF4FF
skinparam SequenceDividerFontColor #41505F
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F6F1FC
skinparam SequenceGroupBorderColor #CDBCE8
skinparam SequenceGroupHeaderFontColor #41505F
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF6EC
skinparam noteBorderColor #F3B27A

actor "Operator / CI" as op
participant "Ansible\ncontrol node\n(localhost)" as ans
database "S3 backend\ntfstate (eu-west-3)" as s3
participant "Swarm server\nmanager-1, single node\n(SSH root)" as srv

== Play 1 - Discover the server from Terraform state (localhost) ==
op -> ans : ansible-playbook playbook.yml\nAWS creds + SSH_PRIVATE_KEY_B64
ans -> ans : assert required env vars
ans -> s3 : GET terraform.tfstate
s3 --> ans : state JSON
ans -> ans : parse outputs\n(manager_public_ip,\nOrigin CA cert + key, no_log)
ans -> ans : delete local state copy (sensitive)
ans -> ans : write SSH key to tempfile (0600)
ans -> ans : add_host -> group swarm\n(single host)

== Play 2 - Provision Docker Engine (hosts: swarm, over SSH) ==
ans -> srv : harden SSH\n(key-only, sshd_config.d)
ans -> srv : add Docker apt repo,\ninstall Docker CE + python3-docker
ans -> srv : write /etc/docker/daemon.json\n(log rotation, validated)
ans -> srv : bridge modules + sysctls
ans -> srv : guard: fail if /opt/dropicture/data\nis still a symlink to the old volume
note over srv
  migration from the old setup:
  rsync the Hetzner volume content
  to the local disk, drop the link,
  then re-run the playbook
end note
ans -> srv : create data dirs on the local SSD\n/opt/dropicture/data/{postgres,\ndragonfly, garage/meta, garage/data}
ans -> srv : write Origin CA cert + key\nto /opt/dropicture/tls (0644 / 0600)
ans -> srv : flush handlers\n(restart docker if needed)

== Play 3 - Initialise the single-node Swarm (SSH) ==
ans -> srv : docker swarm init\nadvertise/listen = public IP:2377
note over srv
  the server is its own manager
  no join, no tokens
  2377/7946/4789 listen publicly but
  stay unreachable: the Hetzner
  firewall only allows 22/80/443/ICMP
end note

== Play 4 - Configure the Swarm (SSH) ==
ans -> srv : store Swarm config\ndropicture_origin_cert
ans -> srv : store Swarm secret\ndropicture_origin_key (no_log)
ans -> srv : create /opt/dropicture/stacks

== Play 5 - Clean up (localhost) ==
ans -> ans : remove temporary SSH key

@enduml